al psychologists, and psychoanalysts. "The rejection of hindsight, with the insistence on trying to see events from the point of view of the participants, was a governing theme with Potter. . . . This sounds like a truism. Watching him apply it however, is a revelation."—Walter Clemons, Newsweek "The best short book on national character I have seen . . . broadly based, closely reasoned, and lucidly written."—Karl W. Deutsch, Yale Review  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aNational characteristics, American. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1890-1959z978311063535540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226676319423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226676319/original  a978-3-11-063535-5  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1890-1959c1890d1959  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles